The paper proposes two efficient Bloom Multifilters for solving multiple set matching problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with membership queries and data filtering, which are common topics in the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Bloom filters in information retrieval (cs.IR), which further supports the possibility of it belonging to this sub-category. The paper also discusses the optimization of space efficiency, which is a common topic in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for determining the suitable structure for improved performance, which is a topic in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
